properties.description:
The width of each item/child.

If number is provided, it is treated as pixels.

If string is provided, it is treated as a CSS width value (%, px, em, rem, etc).

If a percentage (%) is provided, the item is sized based on the carousel container's width

properties.description:
The trailing Badge for use in the ChipFilter.

If a trailingIcon is provided the Badge will **not** be visible.

properties.name: trailingIcon
properties.description:
The trailing icon of the chip.

You can only have one of the trailing options, trailingIcon **or** trailingBadge. If both are present the trailingIcon will be visible.

properties.name: callback
properties.description:
An optional callback function that is invoked when an arrow key is pressed. This function receives the key name, the keyboard event, and the next active element ID. If the function returns 
`true` , the default navigation behavior is prevented; if it returns 
`false`
 or is not provided, the default behavior proceeds.

properties.name: defaultActiveId
properties.description:
The ID of the element that should be active by default. If not provided, the first ID in the 
`ids`
 array will be used.

properties.name: ids
properties.description:
An array of string IDs representing the navigable elements. These IDs should correspond to the 
`id`
 attributes of the elements in the DOM. Ensure the elements are not disabled.

properties.name: increments
properties.description: Optional configuration to set navigation direction increments.

properties.name: arrowRef
properties.description: A ref object for the arrow element.

properties.name: hide
properties.description: Whether to hide the floating element.

properties.name: offsetOptions
properties.description: The offset options for the floating element.

properties.name: placement
properties.description:
The preferred placement of the floating element.

This determines where the floating element will be positioned relative to the reference element.

properties.name: refWidth
properties.description: When set to true, the width of the floating element will match the width of the reference element.

properties.name: strategy
properties.description:
The positioning strategy ('absolute' or 'fixed').

When set to 'fixed', the floating element will be positioned relative to the viewport.

When set to 'absolute', the floating element will be positioned relative to the nearest positioned ancestor.
